Target: OntoPlot is an ontology developed to describe the attributes of land plots and their buildable spaces.

Comment: Average depth represent average plot depth resulting from averaging sample depths along the plot's front edges
Label: Average Depth

Comment: Average width represent average plot width resulting from averaging sample widths along the plot's side edges.
Label: Average Width

Comment: Buildable Space is the maximum allowable space on a plot that can built up according to relevant planning regulations. Buildable spaces may be linked to a Zone, LandUse or a particular Programme if there exist specific regulations. For instance, a plot on which flat and condominium developments are allowed, will have two buildable spaces - one for condominium and one for flat as a product of unique planning regulation combinations.
Label: Buildable Space

Comment: Footprint defines a boundary within which a specific storey exist.
Label: Footprint

Comment: A plot is an area of land that is often delineated with a physical boundary to denote land ownership rights. It is frequently adopted as a basic spatial unit for a cadastre or land registration system.
Label: Plot

Comment: Site area or plot area.
Label: Site Area

Comment: Storey refers to the spaces that within Buildable Space that are at the same height and does not require vertical connections.
Label: Storey

Comment: Storey aggregate defines Buildable Space volume in storeys. Each buildable space will have one storey aggregate, consisting of multiple storeys.
Label: Storey Aggregate

Comment: Building Edge is an uninterupted set of storeys starting from the groundfloor that share the same setback and form a uniform volume.
Label: Building Edge

Comment: A relationship to assign the setback to the specified storey.
Label: at storey

Comment: A relationship that links the storey to its storey aggregate.
Label: contains storey

Comment: A relationship that links the allowed zone use for the specified buildable space.
Label: for zoning case

Comment: A relationship that links the allowed absolute height for the specified buildable space.
Label: has allowed absolute height

Comment: A relationship that links the allowed building edge for the specified buildable space.
Label: has allowed building edge

Comment: A relationship that links the allowed  gross floor area for the specified buildable space.
Label: has allowed gross floor area

Comment: A relationship that links the allowed gross plot ratio for the specified buildable space.
Label: has allowed gross plot ratio

Comment: A relationship that links the allowed site coverage for the specified buildable space.
Label: has allowed site coverage

Comment: A relationship that links the allowed storey aggregate for the specified buildable space.
Label: has allowed storey aggregate

Comment: A relationship that links the required party wall for the specified buildable space.
Label: has required party wall

Comment: A relationship that links the required setback for the specified buildable space.
Label: has required setback

Comment: A relationship that links the allowed floor to floor height for the specified storey.
Label: has allowed floor to floor height

Comment: A relationship that links the allowed footprint for the specified storey.
Label: has allowed footprint

Comment: A relationship that defines the area of anything.
Label: has area

Comment: A relationship that defines the area of a footprint.
Label: has footprint area

Comment: A relationship that defines the area of a plot
Label: has site area

Comment: A relationship that links the buildable space for the specified plot.
Label: has buildable space

Comment: A relationship that indicates the depth for the specified plot.
Label: has depth

Comment: A relationship that indicates the neighbouring plot for the specified plot.
Label: has neighbour

Comment: A relationship that defines the road type of a plot.
Label: has owner

Comment: A relationship that defines the price of a specified plot.
Label: has price

Comment: A relationship that indicates the width for the specified plot.
Label: has width

Comment: A relationship that defines the level of the storey instance.
Label: at level

Comment: A relationship that defines the level of detail for the buildable space.
Label: at level of detail

Comment: A relationship that defines the number of storey for a storey aggregate.
Label: has number of storeys

Comment: A relationship that defines the road type of a plot.
Label: has road type

Comment: A relationship that indicates if the plot is a corner plot or not.
Label: is corner plot

Comment: A relationship that indicates if the plot is found at the residential fringe or not.
Label: at residential fringe
